				<script>paragraph_module[304137] = [{"order":"1","event_name":"paragraph-1-email-signup","user_logged_in":"1"},{"order":"2","event_name":"paragraph-1-subscribe","user_logged_in":"1"},{"order":"3","event_name":"paragraph-1-donate","user_logged_in":""},{"order":"4","event_name":"paragraph-1-takeaction","user_logged_in":""},{"order":"5","event_name":"paragraph-1-travel","user_logged_in":""},{"order":"6","event_name":"paragraph-1-wineclub","user_logged_in":""}];</script> <p>Donald Trump’s <a href="https://www.ajc.com/news/national-govt—politics/text-president-trump-state-the-union-address/aQigG5kw2bUh2xEkJpPSKI/">State of the Union Address</a> did not feature a musical soundtrack. But, if it had, surely the orchestral accompaniment would have soared when he got to the line: “We are born free, and we will stay safe. Tonight, we renew our resolve that America will <em>never</em> be a socialist country.”<aside class="ad right most-popular-plus-ad grey_back">
				<div id="ad-halfpage-304137-0" class="sailthru_class_form"></div>
