<p>Perhaps that is because, while Trump may think “socialism” is a scare word, and while many prominent Democrats may get scared when it is referenced, Sanders is comfortable discussing the ideology. “Do they think I’m afraid of the word? I’m not afraid of the word,” <a href="https://www.thenation.com/article/bernie-sanders-speaks/">says Sanders</a>.
<p>On Tuesday night, the senator trumped Trump’s “born free… stay safe” rhetoric with <a href="https://twitter.com/SenSanders/status/1093004220054323200">a simple observation</a>: “People are not truly free when they can’t afford health care, prescription drugs, or a place to live. People are not free when they cannot retire with dignity or feed their families.”				<aside class="ad-300">
				<div class="ad full-width-mobile inline_ad_300x250_304137" id="inline_ad_300x250_304137"></div>
			</aside>
				
	<script >
		/*
		 * Article Inline Ads Calling
		 */
